               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName corresp="INS0065AMQ">Ë&#x81;Addigrat Qirqos / AMQ</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1850" notAfter="1900">The colophon indicates that the Ms.
                        was completed on the 14th year after the coronation of King Bäkaffa, but he
                        ruled only 9 years (1721-30); it contains also two other dates which appear
                        to be incorrect. Despite the information in the colophon, the script does
                        not look so old palaeographically. The Ms. may date into a later period,
                        second half of the 19th cent. The binding (boards covered with tooled
                        leather) appears to be older than the text block. The Ms. (and the colophon)
                        may be a copy of another 18th-cent. Ms. of Haymanot ʾabäw.</origDate>
                  </origin>
